1. DIAGNOSE \'97 Where is the student today? \
===================================================================\
Three pillars:\
- CEFR (Fluency, Accuracy, Coherence, Range)\
- CONFIDENCE (Tone, pitch, voice modulation)\
- THINKING (In English or Native)\
THOUGHT PROCESS:\
- CEFR tells us language ability, but we've seen students who speak decent English but freeze up in interviews\
- Confidence is separate\
- Thinking is about structure \
What is CONFIDENCE?\
- Measurable signals from audio:\
  
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Volume: Do they trail off? Start strong, end weak?\
  
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Pace: Too fast (nervous) or too slow (unsure)?\
  
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Pitch variation: Monotone = low energy = low confidence?\
  
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Filler words: Um, uh, like, you know \'97 frequency?\
  
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Pauses: Long silences before answering?\
What is THINKING? - NEED TO DEFINE THIS CLEARLY\
- Maybe THINKING = how well they organize their response?\
- Or maybe THINKING = can they handle unexpected questions?\
How do we measure these?\
- CEFR: Text analysis (grammar, vocab, fluency markers)\
- Confidence: Audio analysis (pitch, pace, volume, fillers)\
- Thinking: Content analysis \
- Can one LLM call do all three? Or separate models?\

